{"action": "edit", "code": "def change_color_at_locations(locations: List[Tuple[int, int]], color: int, grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    \"\"\"\n    Changes the color at the given locations in the grid to the given color.\n    \n    Parameters:\n    locations (List[Tuple[int, int]]): The locations to change the color at.\n    color (int): The new color to set at the given locations.\n    grid (np.ndarray): The input grid.\n    \n    Returns:\n    np.ndarray: The updated grid with the new color set at the given locations.\n    \"\"\"\n    for loc in locations:\n        grid[loc[0], loc[1]] = color\n    return grid\ndef get_color_locations(color: int, grid: np.ndarray) -> List[Tuple[int, int]]:\n    \"\"\"\n    Returns a list of tuples representing the locations of the given color in the grid.\n    \n    Parameters:\n    color (int): The color to search for.\n    grid (np.ndarray): The input grid.\n    \n    Returns:\n    List[Tuple[int, int]]: A list of tuples representing the locations of the given color in the grid.\n    \"\"\"\n    return list(zip(*np.where(grid == color)))\ndef main(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    out = input_grid\n    for color in range(2, 10):\n        loc1 = get_color_locations(color, out)\n        loc2 = middle_locations(loc1)\n        out = change_color_at_locations(loc1, color, out)\n    return out\ndef middle_locations(locations: List[Tuple[int, int]]) -> List[Tuple[int, int]]:\n    \"\"\"\n    Returns a list of tuples representing the middle locations of the given locations.\n    \n    Parameters:\n    locations (List[Tuple[int, int]]): The input locations.\n    \n    Returns:\n    List[Tuple[int, int]]: A list of tuples representing the middle locations of the given locations.\n    \"\"\"\n    x = [loc[0] for loc in locations]\n    y = [loc[1] for loc in locations]\n    middle_x = (max(x) + min(x)) // 2\n    middle_y = (max(y) + min(y)) // 2\n    return [(middle_x, middle_y)]", "user_code": "def main(input_grid: np.ndarr